name: Jimmy Carter
summary: Former President Jimmy Carter has received his 10th Grammy nomination for his spoken-word album, "Last Sundays in Plains." At 100 years old, Carter is the oldest person to ever receive a Grammy nomination. The album features Carter's sermons and reflections on faith, hope, and the human condition. If Carter wins, he will become the oldest Grammy winner ever. The current record is held by Ramsey Lewis, who was 80 years old when he won in 2019. Carter's nomination has been met with praise and congratulations from across the political spectrum. He is a renowned humanitarian and Nobel Peace Prize laureate, and his work has been an inspiration to people around the world.
